caption: The service was great!!! The staff was so helpful...and fast!!!! The food was seasoned well and the atmosphere was chill 💚💚definitely a return customer!!! I had the original Pete dog🌭 with waffle fries 🍟😍😜 #stylzbycc  @hairdivacc
My kids loved the wafle fries and corndog,the service is fast,the food really good!
Great place and great value for what you get!
The onion strings are super good! Will come back to try the chicken sandwich.
The Chicago dog is perfection! *chefs kiss*
The Chicago dog is my jam.
O m g. I was right there and missed all this delicious looking food. Sad face. I’m coming back for those fries - 👌🏾
The hot rod combo with onion straws is my go-to. Love the charcoal grilled flavor and the buns are great too.
Food was great and service was 10/10
Good food😋, appealing restaurant, kind & patient service!
Good dogs

The food here is really good. Can’t go wrong with their Chicago dog. Will definitely come back to try the rest of their food. They have an assortment of all sorts of Hot dogs and sausages. You can even build your own. Their fries are phenomenal and they even serve beer (local craft and domestic). It’s right across the street from halfway crooks and is in a really booming area of Atlanta. I can see this place being a hit in the summer/warmer temperatures
Me and my girl are from Pennsylvania and we love hotdogs. We had to check this place out and we were not disappointed.
Great hot dogs and Hero donuts is next door

Cute hotdog spot that the family can enjoy together. Very tasty dogs! Inside (small space) but they offer covered outdoor seating tables. The worker also dressed up as the Hotdog. Forgot to snap his pic 😑

Surprisingly good hotdog experience. The food was good, the draft beer selection was good, and the scenery from their very nice patio brought back memories. I wish this place existed while the Braves were at Turner Field.
Man this was a real treat! Good food good service!!!

This is a great new hotdog spot by GA State Stadium(Turner Field). Had the lil peter version of the skyline coney & the Pete's Special. Can you say FIRE!! I really appreciate that toasted bun and the craft of the hotdog. Loaded, but not super messy. This spot is easily a contender for one of the best hotdog places in the city already. AND they have free parking(a big plus)& a sitting patio area in the back behind the building. I'll be back...soon
Some of the best hot dog in pinto beans I've ever had and quick and friendly
Friendly & Very Tasty !! Love the outside dining area
(Translated by Google) Friendly staff..  It's delicious..  Great location..  The atmosphere is good....  (Original) 직원 친절하구요..  맛 있구요..  위치 좋구요..  분위기도 굿....
Food was great ! Waffle fries, collard green slaw, the banger, Pete original, and the average joe. Bathroom clean, friendly and great customer service !
Great Hot dogs..very tasty, fresh and hot...service quick! Would definitely recommend and will visit next time I'm in town.

As a hotdog lover, this was an amazing find. They have a variety of dogs to choose from so you can find one you are sure to like and yes this includes you vegans! I bought two because I didn't know how large they were and I'm embarrassed to say I ate then both. Oh well! The fries were fried a little to hard but I could tell that if prepared properly they would have been a fantastic complement to the meal.  I'll definitely be visiting again in the near future.
The Chicago Dog along with onion straws were excellent!!!
Been going here since they opened and I must say they have gotten better and better. They have tweaked some areas and it shows.  I love the Beyond Hotdog . Amazing.

This place is really fun! Food is always consistently great, service is fast and pleasant, seating area is clean. They have a nice outdoor seating area that feels pretty covid safe when not crowded. Parking is very easy and free.. A great little gem in Summerhill!
A small building with big character. This place is great
Every hot dog we have had has been amazing. The buns really put them over the top. Waffle fries are top notch as well.
Good food
BEST HOT DOG + WAFFLE FRIES EVER!! So nice, great customer service and perfect outdoor set up w heating for covid friendly dining w the pup, hot dogs and a beer!! 🌭🍟🐶🍺
Delicious

Great hot dogs! Tons of different options for different dogs and builds. Their new chicken sandwich options are really delicious as well. Strong selection of sides, their waffle fries are my personal favorite. Staff is super friendly and welcoming. Highly recommend.

Favorite hot dog place until today. My girlfriend asked for more ketchup and the cashier did not want to give her anymore insisting there was some already in the bag which there wasn’t any once we checked!! And there was literally only like 7 fries in both of our combos. Very disappointed in this place.
Super. Friendly staff, food is delicious, lots of choices, excellent parking, beer to go, trendy neighborhood. Definitely will be going again.
Good food very friendly staff. My new chicken place! Great for rainy Sunday afternoon

Had a friend recommend Hot Dog Pete’s and it is indeed an awesome little hot dog joint. This location is near the old Turner Field in an area that is quickly becoming a cool place to visit with other nearby restaurants. The staff was great and answered all her questions and the prices were very fair. I had the Hot Rod dog and the collard green coleslaw. Both were on point and definitely something I would choose again. If you’re looking for a reason to visit the Summerhill neighborhood in Atlanta, now you have it.
The toasted bun was delicious, however the hot dog meat was  tough. I wouldn't  recommend this  place to anyone.

The Chicago dog was great. Fries have a good taste to them as well. Only complaint was I placed my order online, was supposed to be ready before I arrived, and wasn't prepared until I arrived, so had to wait a little while.
Absolutely delicious!!  I was raised in Birmingham and grew up on Sneaky Pete's hotdogs.  So glad he opened up a store here!!!
It was ok. Good idea and location if I go to a GSU game
Simply exquisite food and outstanding service!
Hot dog was delicious but quantity of French Fries was quite Small.
Over priced and small portions were of food. I could of made a better Hot dog at home.. Very disappointed
False vegan signs. I hope they fix in the future.
Very pricey but worth it the kids liked it and so did we. Get the Jr Pete's so u can try different types the 3 pack and fries will feel u up

Love this place! Feels like I'm in California eating on the patio in the back... Food is great... You have to find your topping of choice (I like the original-it's simple) and I have the beyond sausage... Great service too!
Excellent service and quality...
Not a fan of beans in my chili. It tasted like it came from a can of Hormel.
Finally  Chicago Dog!!!
Food was good. Staff was courteous. And the wait wasn't long. I'll be back

I just came in to try there Vegan Plant Based Sausage Hot Dog? Only to find out that the Bread that they use is not even Vegan! So why would u sell a product plant based if you can't even get the full benefits of it. Makes no sense... Hopefully the owner realizes and does something about this very soon. I was pretty disappointed. Thank you.
Great tasting hot dog and several choices of healthy sides.
Very clean, safe eatery. Tasty dogs at a reasonable price. FGood draft beer selection.
I come here just about once every other week. The hotdogs are absolutely tasty. And the chili is phenomenal.
Good Dogs, great service. Would highly recommend.

Love this new spot that we found on Atlanta Eats! Friendly fast service and great food, would come again! The only thing is I wish the cheese was melted more for the chili cheese dogs cause it kinda falls off and makes it feel like your food is cold. Still 5 stars though. I also love that having a straw is optional great idea with the sippy cup lids.

Today I spotted a hot dog joint. I wanted to go to a neighborhood restaurant so I tried this place. The hot dog was delicious! I thought it was pricey, but it was worth every penny. I had the slaw dog and it was fresh and tasty. The lightly toasted bun with the chilli and slaw  made an amazing hot dog. I can’t wait to try another hot dog.
Great addition to the neighborhood! Fast, good, and great service.
Great dogs,  milk shake was incredible.

Bomb hot dogs 😍 I love the vibe here and happy for the new hot dog place in Atlanta! They have an open patio with cute lights and all. You pick a hotdog and then pick a build. They have their own parking in the back and they're located on a street with other urban bars.

I called Ian in their customer service seems to be OK. If it's Your FIRST time trying there dogs... You may want to Eat There, because the TOGO experience is very Sloppy (they should really get better fitted specialized hot dog containers). #iSERGthat the SLAW DOG was best to me (it would have been even better with cheese), & Pete's Original was best to Bae (who also had a Banger/Viking/& Hot Rod). I also tried Pete's Special dog with the Greek meat, I really didn't notice a difference compared to the regular meat in the chili. I ordered the onion strings as a side, but I really should have got regular fries instead because I only use the onion strings as extra hot dog topping which they were perfect for. The weirdest thing is they're loaded waffle fries because online I didn't notice they add yellow mustard to it which I thought was a cheese sauce, I think the yellow mustard should be optional on the fries, but they weren't that bad. Again that collard green coleslaw was everything they should really offer it on some of everything, the spicy kick to it was perfect and the flavor wasn't overpowering. Be prepared because the chili and most of their toppings excluding the collard green coleslaw has a sour beer/mustard-based taste to it, adding some ketchup may help. I tried their root beer float, the White ice cream taste as if it contained coconut so I wouldn't call it vanilla & really didn't enjoy it. I would still like to try their corn dog tho!
Nice place with medium seating, kids love it. But the prices are over the top for what you get just for hotdogs. The floats are good...
A must visit

Great Service! Very clean, i felt comfortable sitting outside. Hotdog was very tasty, i had just a basic with mustard,chili, onions. Slaw on the side so i could  try it first. Preferred it on the side. Fries are awsome and the onion strings are the BOMB! Great spot for family.

1st timer.  Had the Superior dog in Cinci fashion and wasn't disappointed!  The dog has a wonderful flavor & bite.  Chili was cinnamon-less (unlike the traditional nasty nati's) but was totally  on point.  The bun is what you have come to expect from Alons.  One, if not the best in ATL for dogs.  I'll always be back!
It should be a crime to sell hot dogs this good next to the corpses of two former ballparks.
Clean, decently valued, tasty food options with impeccable customer service and convenient parking in a beautiful neighborhood.  What else can you reasonably ask for?
Slaw dog is the truth! Great environment. This place is going to grow rapid fast

Very exspencive. Not fresh n hot enough.My expectations were expecting a great hotdog that was better than the Varsity dog. Or better that the Georgia Tech hotdog place. And it was not. I bought 4 hotdogs only. It came to $30.46 no fry,no drink,just one hotdog in each box and two bags a lot of packaging. I think that's what I paid for. Staff was friendly though. Thanks,but it's a no go for me. Oh oh... My stomach is hurting. 2stars for the friendly staff.

I’ll start off by saying I loved their French fries! I ordered the loaded fries and the plain. The loaded fries were okay but the plain were awesome! The hot dog (slaw dog) was nothing to brag about but I haven’t tried all of their dogs so next time I will definitely give others a chance. The atmosphere was nice but not clean. The outside seating is awesome but it was a little dirty. There was food underneath the tables and on as well. The staff was super helpful though! If I could change one thing I would love for them to carry hot sauce. I put hot sauce on everything. Lol! Other than that I can definitely say I do want to give them another shot, and I’ll definitely be back to try more dogs.

Next time I want a hotdog I’m just going to Cook Out. This was OK. It wasn’t great and it wasn’t bad it was just good. I had the slaw dog which was made with collard greens. I had to loaded fries which was made with mustard and shredded cheese and chili. They were OK too.
Fast and convenient
Fast and friendly service also great hot dogs 🌭
Amazing
Really good! Amazing staff! Friendly and quick! Couldn't ask for more from a hot dog place

Some of the best hot dogs I can recall having.  Their model was already designed for the present climate:  1) They get your order quickly and get you out the door  2) The majority of the seating is setup outside so there is very little worry about congregating indoors.  3) They are hot dogs so they are easy to take with you if it is a to go order.  They have quite a few combinations of dog/toppings that I would like to come back and try.  Although I think it was the bun that really sold me, it's so delicious  I know hot dogs don't typically sounds that intriguing and are often thought of as being for bbqs and sporting events, but I assure you it's worth a try.
Has vegetarian options!

Order the Lil Peter versions of the Build dogs to try a great variety. We ordered the first 4 on the menu and were happy.  Pete’s Special was our favorite followed by Pete’s Original. And Josh is an awesome manager! Give that man a raise 😀
Amazing quality, variety, and service! I had a great first experience here and Josh was super helpful and friendly. I’ll definitely be back!

The dogs are great! Love the bun bread they use and the different choice options. Wish they had a Chicago dog option. Josh is super friendly and a hard worker. I’ve been here a few times already and he’s usually here and ready to help. The outdoor seating is perfectly covered to protect you from sun and rain and there are fans.
Great food at a reasonable price. Not to mention excellent service from Josh and the crew!
Friendly Great Atmosphere, Amazing Customer service. And the food was delicious
YUM! Our first time here- we'll definitely be back! The food was good and there were enough options to keep all of our friends happy, from the carnivores to the vegans.

This place was great! The fries were very crispy and we'll seasoned. The beyond meat green thumb dog was awesome! Nice little kick from the picco . My wife enjoyed her jalapeno dog dressed up as the rod but something about it seemed a little off for her. She got the loaded fries but again a similar thing. The shakes were very thick so I suggest if you happen to have larger straws at the house ( we took our food home) replace them or it will be a bit of a struggle. The place was very clean and the staff was very friendly. Definitely recommend this place and look forward to going back in the future
So good!! Love all the choices!

My visit was not tasty as my desire for a good hot dog. My food was over cooked. Onion straws were a pile of crunchy graffiti, like I received the crumbs from the last in the bag. My beef hot dog was dry and fell from the bottom of the bun when you picked it up. Questionable if I would revisit.
I was craving a hot dog and we found this new place in Summerhill. Very creative menu, and the food is quality too!

The food and the customer service is top-notch here! We stumbled on this place right after they opened and have already been back a few times. The hot dogs were awesome. The buns were delicious. The toppings were fresh and plentiful. This stuff is delicious!
This place is awesome! The jalapeno cheddarwurst was amazing! This was my 1st visit so I'll have to go back and try more but if it's anything like today's meal, I'm sure it will be great!
Clean, fast and extremely yummy. Josh and the entire staff made us feel at home. The Sonora was outstanding as well as the location and outdoor seating.

So there is a new Hot Dog Joint in town.... and it is totally worth it!  Serving up optional links such as Chicken & Apple, Cheddarwurst  or Vegan combined with their preset or custom toppings you can't go wrong. Really you can't. My least favorite is still pretty decent.  Hot Dog/Sausage size(s) are plentifully.  Customer service skills are on point. So if you have any questions feel free to ask. Facilities are kept clean. Indoor and Outdoor seating available. Parking is around back or across the street. Haven't tried a lot of side items so yeah.... By the way, the Lil' Peter is a perfect size snack.
Awesome hot dogs, great topping options. And really good shakes, just looking for when they add beer.
Great food, great customer service. It's a lovely addition to the neighborhood
I enjoyed the food I ate. It was waffles fries smothered with chili, Pico de Gallo (I think) cheddar cheese onions plus ketchup and mustard.  The prices are reasonable. Check it out!

Service was incredibly nice, they brought my food and checked up on me. I honestly cheaped out on a drink cause I'm on a budget but they were empathetic and asked if I just wanted water because of the moody Georgia sun.  Hotdog was tasty, had a nice spin on it. Would have loved chili cheese fries but I went with the waffle fries. I'd come back to try the rest of the menu.  Note: they got retail parking across the street, so you can get ice cream later. If anything, check out JD grocery store nearby for Jamaican chicken!
Great hotdogs and toppings.
This place was beyond delicious. Everything was so fresh. Seasoned well. I’ll be dreaming about these hot dogs for a week.
Delicious food, shady outdoor bench seating, friendly staff. One of the best chocolate shakes around! I had the Hot Rod with cheddarwurst and a side of cucumber feta salad.
Really good hotdogs, great customer service and the place was very clean.

Good hot dogs and buns... Toppings varied in my happiness, but different.  Worth giving a shot again.  Thought onion straws were overcooked, but the special meat sauce and hot dog sauce were good.  We'll be back because we like certain ingredients a lot.
Love the impossible sausage. And waffle fries are the best!
Food were good the first time I was there but today  07.02.20 the onions straws were awful at $3.49 smh not so good anymore I'm done.
If you're in the Atlanta area and want a good lunch. Stop by Hot Dog Petes. Great food, loaded fries are amazing. Try them

This little cute hot dog place in the heart Of Atlanta is a gem!! I'm in love with the "Green Thumb" hotdog. I met the GM Alii and he's the BEST. He was very professional, knowledgeable, and he paid attention to each customer's needs. I will definitely be back OFTEN!! Thanks to the staff at Hotdog Pete's for making every visit memorable.
Love the dogs and crispy waffle fries! Great customer service too

AMAZING! MUST VISIT!!! I love hot dogs and its rather difficult finding a place to try different types of hot dogs. I'm so glad that Hot Dog Pete's opened!  The service was top notch and a true embodiment of southern hospitality. The interior is quaint and nicely laid out. There's an outdoor sitting area with nice large umbrellas. It was a treat to sit outside and enjoy my meal. Now to the whole reason you come here, THE FOOD.  The food is amazing. You choose a weiner and then you choose a build for the hot dog. You can also make it a combo if you want. I got the superior dog with the skyline coney build and loaded fries. The hot dog was truly one of the best, if not the best, hot dog I've ever had. The bun was nicely toasted as well as the hot dog itself. The chili was great and everything came together perfectly. I didn't even get a chance to take a picture because I just devoured it.  Anyway, come by and try it for yourself. You'll love the food and service!
Just ordered Hot Dog Pete’s on DoorDash and we were blown away.  Great bread, excellent toppings, and generous portions.  We will definitely be back:)
It’s so good it’s like no hotdog I have ever tasted before and their manager is so nice
Best hotdogs in town.

Got the supreme dog skyline style with waffle fries and a corn dog! Delicious, we’ve been waiting for these hot dogs and we (me and the wife) were not disappointed! In fact, “oh my god, I love hot dogs” was the official statement. We will 100% be back for more!

I have tried three different hot dogs from Pete's and each one is unique and better than the next. The dogs are filling with a great bun and interesting toppings. I ordered mine with a side of seasoned fries and shake to enjoy on the patio. Even my vegetarian girlfriend loved the veggie dog and cucumber feta salad! A great addition to Summerhill.
We had an opportunity to taste The Hot Rod and Sonora hot dogs. Both were good. Liked the collard slaw too!
